Somali Lawmakers Back Ali as New Prime Minister, Somalia Report Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-06-28T10:55:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/somali-lawmakers-back-ali-as-new-prime-minister-somalia-report-says.html
Somali lawmakers approved the
nomination of Abdiweli Mohamed Ali as prime minister,  Somalia
Report  said, without saying how it got the information.  Ali, a former deputy prime minister, received the backing
of 437 lawmakers, with six abstentions, the Nairobi-based online
 news agency  said on its website today.  Somali President Sheikh Sharif Sheikh Ahmed chose Ali as
prime minister after his predecessor, Mohamed Abdullahi Mohamed,
resigned as part of a deal to extend the mandate of the current
transitional federal government by one year to August 2012.  Mohamed must select a new cabinet within 30 days, which
legislators need to approve, Somalia Report said. Ali, a former
associate professor of economics at Niagara University, served
previously as minister of planning and international
cooperation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net . 